caption: Might be the best Thai in Frederick. Prompt service, good food, friendly staff...not sure what else one might need.

Soooo many delicious options! The pa-nang curry was so amazing that I was inspired to try making it on my own! The thai tea is delicious, and if you spend $50 you get a free appetizer. I highly recommend this restaurant if you love Thai food!

Have always liked the food here. I just wish the staff were more friendly. We placed an order for $50 worth of carryout, tipped 20% as we always have during these tough times, and upon picking it up one of the staff couldn't even a muster up a "hello" or a "thank you." My husband accidentally knocked into their pen holder, offered to pick it up, and the dude acted annoyed. As much as I like the food, I'd rather go someplace where our business is appreciated.

Last week was our first time in this fine restaurant. But It is definitely not the last time. We had a good time with the excellent service, with the high quality  meal and wine and with the honest payment. We will surely visit there in a short time.

On a recent weekend getaway Frederick, my family stumbled upon Sumittra Thai in historic Frederick. Without reservations, we tried going to Cafe Nola or Hootch & Banter, but the wait was too long. We were hungry so Yelp directed us to Sumittra on the same street as Cafe Nola. They opened at noon and had plenty of outdoor seating for our family of three. Here's what we enjoyed:  1) Food: It's quality food. My wife's veggie drunken noodles with extra veggies was well seasoned and my green chicken curry was delicious. It filled us up without making us feel gross.  2) Service: It's so good! The servers are kind, attentive and always anticipated our needs.  3) Atmosphere: The indoor is closed due to the pandemic, but you can still safely go inside to use the restroom. They set up several tables outside on the street.
Second favorite place in downtown fredrick. Best Thai food ever!! Excellent mixed cocktail menu as well👌

I got the Pad See Eew for carry out and it was one of the best things I’ve ever had. The broccoli was favorable and crisp, not the soggy stuff you sometimes get. The chicken was cooked well and the portion was sizable. Will definitely come here again.

I got take-out (ordered ahead of time and picked it up) and the service was amazing. The restaurant was very clean and neat looking. The workers were kind and went above and beyond (one of them even ran down the street to give us a box of rice they forgot about).  The food was amazing and they had lots of vegetarian and vegan options. 100% recommend.
Good food
Love this place..!

Had a great Pad Thai. They have good COVID safety measures, staff were wearing masks. I got Pad Thai to go and it was quickly made, but really tasty with the right amount of sauce, chicken, noodles, scallions, and peanuts. Lunch special $9.95... excellent! Highly recommend.
This place clearly knows how to please their clients. Constantly with a very friendly demeanor. The food is conveniently priced, constantly tasty and clean.

Would highly recommend Sumittra!  I hate to sound basic but the pad thai is amazing, you wont regret it. The Currys are also delicious! Good quality and authentic thai food with very polite service!!
Take out ordered at store. Friendly service. Flavor was great, just wish there was more kick for the spicier dishes.

This is one of our favorite restaurants in town, and definitely our favorite for Thai food. We just picked some up for our anniversary dinner at home. My personal favorites are the crispy spring rolls and the green curry with eggplant, but everything I've had is delicious.

Excellent food that fits within a reasonable budget.  Have been there a few times.  We like to try new places, but whenever we can't agree on a new place we end up here :-) because we all agree on this.

I celebrated my birthday today in this fine place. happy to tell that we enjoyed a tremendous evening and the place was surely the reason for the fruitful evening. The crew  contributed in a pleasant manner, the meals were appetizing and my friends were so  happy. We shall absolutely return for more events. thanks very much.

♡I positively LOVE this place! The service is amazing, and the food is even better! ♡They will cater to your spice tolerance and have non-spicy food. But I am a glutton for punishment and order my dishes extra spicy: 🌶🌶🌶🌶🌶. What I absolutely enjoy the most is that my EXTRA spicy dishes aren't just fire. The dish is still flavorful, savory, sweet, or whatever you ordered. Just with that lovely, lovely burn... a bit on the tounge at first bite but there is always this wonderful afterburn. ♡I would say this is a perfect spot for a date or part of a, "night on the town". Especially if you are a spice fiend like me!

Cozy atmosphere along with quick, friendly, and attentive service. The food was fresh and tasty, particularly the crispy wonton and chicken satay appetizers. Glad we chose Sumittra out of the other possible Thai options in the area!
So good!  Nice staff and the curry is great!

The pad Thai was really good! The noodles had just a hint of that smokiness from the grill, and the flavor was fantastic!  The green curry was cooked really well and a good mix of sweet and spicy. The chicken and vegetables were cooked perfectly, nothing was dry.  The salad was also surprisingly good, some kind of vinegar and sesame oil dressing over mostly cabbage.  We did order some curry puffs that weren't fully hot in the inside, the service was great and they prepared some new ones that were hot!

This place is pretty good. The food is great but the service is the worst I've ever had at a fine dining restaurant. The server kept getting mad at us when he didn't hear and would argue with us if he didn't like our questions. Two of my party had allergies and he didn't know the answers and acted like we didn't ask early enough before ordering the food even though we did. He also insisted that some food didn't have what my friend was allergic to when we looked it up and knew it had that allergen. He was also very rude and when he accidentally gave us an extra order after we clearly had it changed then he argued with us and acted overall unhappy. The last complaint is that in the menu an 18% tip is automatically added to the bill for a six or more party. We were all not happy to pay as the service was so poor and unhappy. I would come back here for the food and atmosphere but again the service was horrible. I would recommend this place to others that love Thai but it would have to be worth it to bare the service to get the amazing food.
Every dish I've gotten of this place has been delicious. The price is not too bad either!

I love Sumittra. Great atmosphere, as a vegetarian/vegan I feel I have so many options from their menu. Their beer is a great price. I come here again and again. One of those places that can offer a fresh meal full of vegetables without unreasonable cost.

The only suggestion I have is that my husband had the pork pad Thai.  There were large slices of pork in there, but they had no flavor. The noodles had plenty of flavor, but the meat had none. It's like the flavor was cooked out of the meat before it went into the dish.  But we will be back to try other things!

Oh man. Where can we start? When you are deliberating what to eat when in downtown Frederick, you wonder “Japanese, Thai, or what?”  If you ever decide to go with Thai, you are probably going to end up at Summitra.  Try their soup, try their curry, try their drunken noodles. All of their food is authentic and is made to please your Thai craving.  Wanna go for super spicy? You better have your tongue ready for some action.  Highly recommend.

The service is nice and very responsive and the food is very well done, each bite was full of flavor with intricacies that enticed the pallet for more. I would say some of the best Thai cuisine in Frederick county. The atmosphere gives the impression of a busy Thai market place, very noisy and crowded for a Saturday evening. When I was there, I had this sense of traveling into a different country, especially with the cool lights and mirrors, it made me question all the theories of time travel and teleportation. I almost gave the place 5 stars for I felt it was to crowded and a little on the pricey side, expect to spend over $100 for a dinner for two with a couple drinks.

Have visited this restaurant frequently since they opened and today, during Presidents Day I ordered again... When I picked up my lunch, instead of the normal price for lunch I am charged almost 4 dollars more and am told that its because of the federal holiday - that they are only selling dinner portion due to the holiday. I explained that I wasn't told about this when I phoned in the order (as this was a pick-up) and that I would not have paid 14.00 for lunch - The place was packed full of patrons The size difference is maybe 1/4 cup more liquid in the green curry and the same amount of rice. My organization has constantly ordered from Sumittra for our parties and meetings - this will certainly have an impact on that decision going forward. If this is considered Normal Practice - it should be announced when placing the order.  As far as I could see, the people inside the restaurant had the same size lunch portions as if I had eaten in.... Shame....
